    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Proverbs",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 27,
        "summary": "Let another man praise you\u2014A prudent man foresees evil\u2014Hell and destruction are never full.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "Boast not thyself of to morrow; for thou knowest not what a day may bring forth.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Boast.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 5
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "James 4:13 (13\u201314).",
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 30
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Let another man praise thee, and not thine own mouth; a stranger, and not thine own lips.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Boast; Humility.",
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 22
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "A stone is heavy, and the sand weighty; but a fool's wrath is heavier than them both.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Esth. 3:5.",
                        "start": 53,
                        "end": 58
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 10
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 59,
                        "end": 61
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Wrath is cruel, and anger is outrageous; but who is able to stand before envy?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Cruelty.",
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 14
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Anger.",
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 25
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 6,
                        "end": 8
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 28
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 51
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Open rebuke is better than secret love.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 28:23.",
                        "start": 5,
                        "end": 11
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 14
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Faithful are the wounds of a friend; but the kisses of an enemy are deceitful.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 141:5; D&C 121:43 (43\u201344).",
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 23
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Friendship.",
                        "start": 29,
                        "end": 35
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Sam. 20:9; Luke 22:48 (47\u201348).",
                        "start": 45,
                        "end": 51
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Deceit.",
                        "start": 68,
                        "end": 77
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 12
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 64,
                        "end": 67
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The full soul loatheth an honeycomb; but to the hungry soul every bitter thing is sweet.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "As a bird that wandereth from her nest, so is a man that wandereth from his place.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 45
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Ointment and perfume rejoice the heart: so doth the sweetness of a man's friend by hearty counsel.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 47
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Thine own friend, and thy father's friend, forsake not; neither go into thy brother's house in the day of thy calamity: for better is a neighbour that is near than a brother far off.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Sam. 9:1.",
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 18:24. TG\u00a0Neighbor.",
                        "start": 136,
                        "end": 145
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 120,
                        "end": 123
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 131,
                        "end": 133
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 146,
                        "end": 153
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "My son, be wise, and make my heart glad, that I may answer him that reproacheth me.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "A prudent man foreseeth the evil, and hideth himself; but the simple pass on, and are punished.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 13
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 34,
                        "end": 37
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 54,
                        "end": 57
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 78,
                        "end": 81
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Take his garment that is surety for a stranger, and take a pledge of him for a strange woman.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 20:16.",
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0foreign woman.",
                        "start": 79,
                        "end": 92
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "He that blesseth his friend with a loud voice, rising early in the morning, it shall be counted a curse to him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Curse.",
                        "start": 98,
                        "end": 103
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "A continual dropping in a very rainy day and a contentious woman are alike.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 19:13.",
                        "start": 2,
                        "end": 11
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 21:19; 3\u00a0Ne. 11:29.",
                        "start": 47,
                        "end": 58
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Whosoever hideth her hideth the wind, and the ointment of his right hand, which bewrayeth itself.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 74,
                        "end": 79
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 90,
                        "end": 97
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Iron sharpeneth iron; so a man sharpeneth the countenance of his friend.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Friendship.",
                        "start": 65,
                        "end": 71
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Whoso keepeth the fig tree shall eat the fruit thereof: so he that waiteth on his master shall be honoured.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Cor. 9:7.",
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 36
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 21:23; 2\u00a0Ne. 6:13; D&C 133:11 (10\u201311).",
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 74
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "As in water face answereth to face, so the heart of man to man.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 26
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Hell and destruction are never full; so the eyes of man are never satisfied.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0The spirit world, place of the dead, is never filled up.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 4
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Eccl. 1:8.",
                        "start": 66,
                        "end": 75
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "As the fining pot for silver, and the furnace for gold; so is a man to his praise.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 2
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 59,
                        "end": 61
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Though thou shouldest bray a fool in a mortar among wheat with a pestle, yet will not his foolishness depart from him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0pound, rub.",
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 26
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 73,
                        "end": 76
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Be thou diligent to know the state of thy flocks, and look well to thy herds.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 5:59 (37\u201360); D&C 20:53 (38\u201360).",
                        "start": 42,
                        "end": 48
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 53
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For riches are not for ever: and doth the crown endure to every generation?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 9:30; Jacob 2:18 (18\u201319).",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 10
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 14
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 48,
                        "end": 54
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The hay appeareth, and the tender grass sheweth itself, and herbs of the mountains are gathered.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The lambs are for thy clothing, and the goats are the price of the field.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 13
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 49
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And thou shalt have goats' milk enough for thy food, for the food of thy household, and for the maintenance for thy maidens.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 19
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 88,
                        "end": 91
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
}